{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782355537201,"sessionID":"ses_10354f7d8ffeJcg46dfqn3CTaB","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_VCuWRku2yHgDqBXSCnhYCm7g","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\agent-inputs\\current-agent-input.md"},"output":"<path>D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\agent-inputs\\current-agent-input.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Agent Input Brief - phase-01-project-skeleton-resources / phase\n2: \n3: This brief is a narrow planning input compiled from current workflow reports. It is not an authority file.\n4: Start here, then open only the referenced source paths, target endpoints, capabilities, or reports needed for the task.\n5: \n6: ## Boundaries\n7: \n8: - Source project: `D:\\Kotlin2Cangjie\\Foodike`\n9: - Target project: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\Foodike-Harmony`\n10: - Translation inputs: `D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs`\n11: - Do not read sibling old translations unless the user explicitly asks for comparison.\n12: - Edit only target project files and agent-maintained authority files required by the current session.\n13: \n14: ## Freshness\n15: \n16: | artifact | exists | generatedAt | phase | error |\n17: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n18: | phaseTaskChecklist | yes | 2026-06-25T02:45:25+00:00 | phase-01-project-skeleton-resources |  |\n19: | phaseGroupVerdicts | no |  |  | missing |\n20: | phaseCapabilityChecklist | yes | 2026-06-25T02:45:26+00:00 | phase-01-project-skeleton-resources |  |\n21: | translationQualitySummary | no |  |  | missing |\n22: | phaseCoverageGate | no |  |  | missing |\n23: | targetStructure | yes | 2026-06-25T02:45:25+00:00 |  |  |\n24: | sourceCoverageMatrix | yes | 2026-06-25T02:01:25+00:00 |  |  |\n25: | platformCapabilityCheck | yes | 2026-06-25T02:01:25+00:00 |  |  |\n26: \n27: ## Scope Rules\n28: \n29: - Treat the current implementation group contract as the primary task input.\n30: - Open the listed source paths and target endpoints before consulting broad phase reports.\n31: - Use full phase reports as indexed references; do not sweep unrelated groups unless this group requires a small shared foundation.\n32: - Update authoritative matrix/capability rows only for this group and any directly required shared surface.\n33: \n34: ## Working Set\n35: \n36: - clusters: _none_\n37: - repair child groups: _none_\n38: - implementation groups: `phase-01-project-skeleton-resources-resource-migration-manifest`, `phase-01-project-skeleton-resources-source-behavior-app`, `phase-01-project-skeleton-resources-source-behavior-kotlin-source`, `phase-01-project-skeleton-resources-resource-migration-res-values`\n39: - features: `app-src-main-androidmanifest-xml-c7c6907eb1-004-android-platform-component-lifecycle-suc`, `app-src-main-androidmanifest-xml-e5fadea668-001-android-resource-configuration-must-be-m`, `app-src-main-androidmanifest-xml-525ca85433-002-intent-uri-bundle-deeplink-or-cross-scre`, `app-src-main-androidmanifest-xml-dcc4612e71-003-runtime-permission-request-permission-re`, `app-src-main-androidmanifest-xml-422b0d36ae-005-screen-lifecycle-entry-point-initializat`, `app-build-gradle-kts-52a26dc1e9-003-android-platform-component-lifecycle-suc`, `app-build-gradle-kts-ab52d0a44d-001-navigation-surface-menu-drawer-toolbar-o`, `app-build-gradle-kts-329cf39b55-002-runtime-permission-request-permission-re`, `app-build-gradle-kts-0a842e752f-004-screen-lifecycle-entry-point-initializat`, `app-build-gradle-kts-aa010bdd3d-005-settings-preferences-option-toggles-or-c`, `build-gradle-kts-6cd8a326ab-002-android-platform-component-lifecycle-suc`, `build-gradle-kts-e6afb1cfd2-001-runtime-permission-request-permission-re`, `build-gradle-kts-2f9b07ef27-003-settings-preferences-option-toggles-or-c`, `app-src-main-res-values-colors-xml-8d1c4a6521-002-android-android-values-file-should-be-ma`, `app-src-main-res-values-colors-xml-8e1c28dae7-001-android-resource-configuration-must-be-m`, `app-src-main-res-values-themes-xml-b98f18ad24-003-android-android-values-file-should-be-ma`, `app-src-main-res-values-themes-xml-1c5ca98798-001-android-resource-configuration-must-be-m`, `app-src-main-res-values-themes-xml-e49ca5e971-002-runtime-permission-request-permission-re`\n40: - capabilities: _none_\n41: - source paths: `app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml`, `app/build.gradle.kts`, `build.gradle.kts`, `app/src/main/res/values/colors.xml`, `app/src/main/res/values/themes.xml`\n42: - target endpoints: _none_\n43: - acceptance evidence: Closed critical/high features must record sourceBehavior, targetBehavior, parityLevel, targetEndpoints, and verificationEvidence.; Build pass alone is not per-feature verification.; Resource inputs must be implemented, mapped to equivalent target behavior, or closed with a specific deferred/replaced reason.\n44: \n45: ## Current Implementation Groups\n46: \n47: | group | priority | type | title | sources | target domains |\n48: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n49: | phase-01-project-skeleton-resources-resource-migration-manifest | critical | resource-migration | Resource migration: manifest | app/src/main/AndroidManifest.xml |  |\n50: | phase-01-project-skeleton-resources-source-behavior-app | critical | source-behavior | Source behavior: app | app/build.gradle.kts |  |\n51: | phase-01-project-skeleton-resources-source-behavior-kotlin-source | critical | source-behavior | Source behavior: kotlin-source | build.gradle.kts |  |\n52: | phase-01-project-skeleton-resources-resource-migration-res-values | high | resource-migration | Resource migration: res/values | app/src/main/res/values/colors.xml, app/src/main/res/values/themes.xml |  |\n53: \n54: ## Plan Contract Alignment\n55: \n56: Plan contract entries are upstream planning evidence. Use them to preserve phase/group ownership, but resolve conflicts through source code and authority JSON records.\n57: - summary: planGroups=2, matchedGroups=2, unmatchedGroups=0\n58: \n59: ### Match